{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":184120,"duration_api_ms":181638,"num_turns":22,"result":"The structured review has been submitted. To summarise the verdict:\n\n**🔶 Changes Requested** — one major issue blocks merge:\n\nThe `all_failures_environment_related()` function matches env patterns against the **concatenated test name + message**, meaning any test whose name contains \"redis\", \"database\", etc. will be misclassified as environment-related even if the failure is a pure code bug. The fix is a one-line jq change (match `.message` only) plus updating the BATS test that currently validates the wrong behaviour. Everything else — constants, counter logic, scope constraint, and overall test coverage — is solid and consistent with existing patterns.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"5ed08a6a-8991-43a2-a26b-2071b0e70af3","total_cost_usd":0.5638105000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":22,"cache_creation_input_tokens":32100,"cache_read_input_tokens":307301,"output_tokens":8377,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":32100,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":22,"outputTokens":8377,"cacheReadInputTokens":307301,"cacheCreationInputTokens":32100,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.5638105000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"result":"changes_requested","summary":"PR #57 correctly implements all 5 acceptance criteria from issue #51: MAX_TEST_ITERATIONS reduced to 7, convergence threshold lowered to 2, MAX_VALIDATION_FIX_ITERATIONS=2 with independent counter, environment error detection added to skip fix-agent dispatch, and scope constraint added to validation fix prompt. Test coverage is thorough (24 new BATS tests for env detection, 9 for constants). One important issue must be resolved before merge: the environment error detection function matches against the test name field in addition to the message field, which can cause false positives and silently skip the fix agent for legitimate code failures.","comments":"## PR #57 Review — Issue #51: Reduce Test Loop Churn\n\n### Part 1 — Spec Review ✅ All ACs Met\n\n| AC | Requirement | Status |\n|----|-------------|--------|\n| AC1 | `MAX_TEST_ITERATIONS=7`, convergence threshold=2 | ✅ |\n| AC2 | `MAX_VALIDATION_FIX_ITERATIONS=2`, independent counter | ✅ |\n| AC3 | Skip fix agent when all failures are env-related | ✅ |\n| AC4 | Scope constraint in validation fix prompt | ✅ |\n| AC5 | BATS tests for all new logic | ✅ |\n\nNo scope creep detected.\n\n---\n\n### Part 2 — Code Quality\n\n**✅ What's Done Well**\n- `exit 2` + `set_final_state` on cap exhaustion is consistent with existing convention (lines 990, 1666, 1877)\n- `|| echo 0` / `|| echo 1` jq fallbacks fail conservatively — never silently misclassify failures\n- Env detection correctly placed after pre-existing-failures check and before convergence detection\n- `log()` uses `\"$*\"` so multi-argument calls concatenate correctly\n- `validation_fix_iteration` is a correct cumulative cap (not reset per outer iteration)\n- 24 BATS tests cover all 10 env patterns, mixed failures, case-insensitivity, missing fields, null, and empty array\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Important — Changes Required\n\n**`all_failures_environment_related()` matches test name field, causing false positives**\n\nThe jq filter concatenates `message + \" \" + test` before matching:\n```jq\n((.message // \"\") + \" \" + (.test // \"\"))\n| test($pat; \"i\")\n```\n\nA test named `redis-connection-behavior` or `database-retry-logic` with a pure code-level failure (wrong return value, broken assertion) would be misclassified as environment-related, silently skipping the fix agent.\n\nThe issue description specifies checking **\"failure descriptions\"** (i.e. messages), not test names. The BATS test `\"pattern found in test name field also counts\"` validates the wrong behaviour.\n\n**Fix:** Match only the `message` field:\n```jq\n[.[] | select(\n    ((.message // \"\"))\n    | test($pat; \"i\")\n    | not\n)] | length\n```\nUpdate the corresponding BATS test to assert that an env keyword in the test name *alone* (with a non-env message) returns status 1.\n\n---\n\n### 💡 Suggestions (Non-blocking)\n\n1. **Convergence triggers after 1 fix attempt**: `sig_count >= 2` exits after the same signature is seen twice, meaning only one fix attempt per failure pattern. Correct per spec, but may be aggressive for multi-file bugs.\n2. **`exit 2` on validation cap blocks downstream stages**: If a PR-review stage is expected to run after validation-fix exhaustion, the hard exit silently skips it. Worth a docblock note.\n3. **Redundant readonly assertions**: `MAX_TEST_ITERATIONS` and `MAX_VALIDATION_FIX_ITERATIONS` are added to the omnibus readonly test but already have dedicated tests — harmless duplication.","issues":[{"description":"all_failures_environment_related() concatenates message + test name before pattern matching. A test named 'redis-connection-behavior' with a pure code-level failure message would be misclassified as environment-related, causing the fix agent to be silently skipped. The issue spec says to check failure *descriptions* (messages), not test names. The jq filter should match only the message field: `((.message // \"\")) | test($pat; \"i\")`. The BATS test 'pattern found in test name field also counts' must also be updated to assert status 1 (env keyword in test name alone should NOT classify as env-related).","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1519,"severity":"major"},{"description":"BATS test 'pattern found in test name field also counts' asserts that an env keyword in the test name field (with a non-env message) returns status 0. This validates incorrect behaviour — a Redis unit test with a code-level failure should not be classified as environment-related. This test should assert status 1 after the jq filter is restricted to the message field only.","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-test/test-environment-error-detection.bats","line":147,"severity":"major"},{"description":"On validation fix cap exhaustion (validation_fix_iteration > MAX_VALIDATION_FIX_ITERATIONS), the code hard-exits with exit 2. If any downstream pipeline stages (e.g. PR review) are expected to run regardless, they will be silently skipped. Consider adding a comment to the function docblock clarifying this hard-exit behaviour is intentional.","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-orchestrator.sh","line":1921,"severity":"minor"},{"description":"MAX_TEST_ITERATIONS and MAX_VALIDATION_FIX_ITERATIONS are added to the omnibus 'timeout constants are readonly' test block, but each already has a dedicated readonly-declaration test. This is harmless but creates redundant assertions.","file":".claude/scripts/implement-issue-test/test-constants.bats","line":223,"severity":"minor"}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"418d6515-8253-446e-8214-417f62ed2fbf"}
